  m_text: Neptune is the most distant planet from the Sun and is an ice giant. It
    has the strongest winds of any planet in the Solar System, which can be over
    1000mph! Neptune is the only planet in our Solar System not visible to the naked
    eye, and was discovered through mathematical methods rather than direct observation.
