  m_text: Saturn is the second largest planet in the Solar System and is a gas giant
    like Jupiter. Saturn has the brightest and largest ring system in the solar system.
    The rings are mostly made off small particles of ice, but there are also particles
    of rock and dust. Saturn has over 146 moons, and its largest moon, Titan, is
    the only moon in the solar system to have its own substantial atmosphere.
