  m_text: Earth is the only planet in our Solar System with liquid water on the surface
    and is the biggest of the four rocky planets nearest the Sun. It has one natural
    satellite, the Moon, which is responsible for the tides. Humans have also launched
    many artificial satellites to help us study the Earth and communicate with each
    other - can you spot one? The Earth is also tilted which causes the seasons -
    use your control panel to find out more!
