  m_text: Jupiter is the largest planet in the Solar System. It is a gas giant -
    mostly made of hydrogen and helium. The dark orange stripes are called belts,
    and the light bands are called zones. Can you spot the Great Red Spot? It is
    a storm, larger than Earth, which has raged for hundreds of years!
