      m_Calls: []
  m_text: Asteroids are rocky objects in orbit around the Sun and most orbit here
    in the main asteroid belt between Mars and Jupiter. The asteroids shown are made
    bigger so you can see them, but in reality some are as small as pebbles. Ceres
    is the largest asteroid in the belt and it's the only dwarf planet located in
    the inner solar system. Turn up the speed again and see how the asteroids closer
    to Mars move faster than those on the outside of the belt nearer to Jupiter.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
