      m_Calls: []
  m_text: Uranus is an ice giant made of water, ammonia and methane. The methane
    absorbs red light, but reflects blue light, which gives the planet its unique
    colour. Uranus appears to spin sideways, or 'roll' around the Sun. Uranus also
    has very faint, dark rings. Uranus is so far away that only one spacecraft has
    ever explored it up close - NASA's Voyager 2 mission.
