  m_text: Venus is the second planet from the Sun and the hottest planet in our Solar
    System due to its thick atmosphere. Venus spins backwards compared to other planets,
    and due to its slow rotation, it is the only planet whose day longer than its
    year. Venus is very similar to Earth in terms of size and gravity.
