  m_text: Mercury is the nearest planet to the Sun and the smallest in our Solar
    System. It has a solid surface made of mostly rocks and metals and is covered
    in huge impact craters. It is named after the Roman god Mercury, who was the
    god of travellers and messenger of the gods - probably because it moves so quickly
    through the sky!
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
